    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1938-07-27T17:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1938-07-27T17:00:00-05:00" n="876"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d876">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">611.6731/412a: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in Turkey</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">MacMurray</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1938-07-27T18:00:00-04:00"
                            >July 27, 1938—6 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>18. The Turkish Ambassador called at the Department on July 25 under instructions
                    from his Government to submit a copy of the Turkish Government’s latest
                        proposal<note n="26" xml:id="d876fn26">
                        <hi rend="italic">Supra.</hi>
                    </note> with respect to the general provisions in the proposed trade agreement
                    relating to binding of duty reductions, exchange control, and duration of
                    agreement. If the Delegation has not yet received a copy of this proposal, you
                    should request one from the Turkish authorities at the earliest opportunity, and
                    telegraph the Department (1) your comments and recommendations with reference
                    thereto and (2) the reasons, if known, for this action on the part of the
                    Turkish Government in transmitting its proposal through the Ambassador here
                    rather than through the Delegation at Ankara.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
